  <h1>Top Attractions in Coorg</h1>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Abbey Falls:</strong> A beautiful waterfall located in the middle of coffee estates. The sight and sound of water crashing amidst greenery is simply refreshing.</li>
    <li><strong>Raja’s Seat:</strong> A popular sunset point in Madikeri, offering panoramic views of the valley. Once a favorite of the Kodava kings, it’s still a royal spot for reflection and photography.</li>
    <li><strong>Dubare Elephant Camp:</strong> An interactive experience where you can observe, bathe, and feed elephants in a natural forest setting. A favorite for families and wildlife lovers.</li>
    <li><strong>Talacauvery & Bhagamandala:</strong> Sacred sites where the mighty Cauvery River originates. Surrounded by hills and clouds, this is a spiritual and scenic highlight.</li>
    <li><strong>Coffee Plantations:</strong> Take a guided tour through Coorg’s famous estates, learn about the coffee-making process, and enjoy a fresh cup of Coorg’s finest brew.</li>
    <li><strong>Madikeri Fort & Omkareshwara Temple:</strong> Explore the town’s historical and cultural side with visits to these significant landmarks.</li>
  </ul>

